<paragraph id="6961E949C6101B25FF6CFFB1FE37FF2A" blockId="22.[151,1436,151,608]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6101B25FF6CFFB1FEAFFF6D" bold="true" box="[199,298,151,176]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" reason="1">Habitat.</emphasis>
The Danish Expedition material of the species was collected in the subtidal zone ranging from 
<quantity id="AE2644ACC6101B25FAE4FFBEFF35FF0E" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="m" value="28.5" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="7.0">
7 to 
<specimenCount id="7FD822C0C6101B25FA2BFFB1FF35FF0E" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="generic">50 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. depth, whereas during the present study it was collected in low-intertidal zone with rocky structure mixed with trapped muddy substrate.
</paragraph>
